    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: code-impl in BFF (.cs file modification, tag bff-api, ADR-013+029+038 applicable) — quality gates Step 9.5 required · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-11 + plan.md Wave 4 + .claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md + task 040 caller-audit doc.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Verify dependencies">
      Confirm `notes/spikes/executeanalysisasync-caller-audit.md` exists (task 040). Confirm Wave 9 task 091 marked ✅ in TASK-INDEX. If either missing, STOP and report.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Enumerate non-chat callers">
      From the audit doc, extract the "Wave 4 task 041 work list" (non-chat callers). If empty, skip to step 9 (verification-only path). If non-empty, proceed step-by-step per caller.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Per caller — read current implementation">
      For each non-chat caller, open the source file. Document: Action invoked, payload shape, return parsing, logging hooks. This is the contract to preserve.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Per caller — choose replacement pattern">
      Per audit-doc disposition:
      - **Consumer-routing path** (named consumer exists): inject `IConsumerRoutingService` + `IInvokePlaybookAi`; call `ResolveAsync(consumerName)` → `InvokePlaybookAsync(playbookId, payload)`. Mirror Wave 9 task 091 SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.
      - **Degenerate-playbook path** (ad-hoc AI call): create a Start→AiAnalysis→ReturnResponse playbook in spaarkedev1 referencing the same Action; replace the call site with `IInvokePlaybookAi.InvokePlaybookAsync(newPlaybookId, payload)`.
      Document which path chosen per caller.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Per caller — refactor call site">
      Replace direct `ExecuteAnalysisAsync` call with the chosen replacement. Preserve: logging, error handling, return-shape parsing. Use `cancellationToken` end-to-end. Maintain DI registration symmetry (Wave 4 task 040 audit flags if registration needs adjustment).
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Per caller — update tests">
      For each refactored caller, update its corresponding test class to mock `IInvokePlaybookAi` (and `IConsumerRoutingService` if consumer-routing path chosen) instead of `IAnalysisOrchestrationService`. Per ADR-038: NO `Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;`, NO DI-registration tests, NO ctor null-check tests.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Build + run tests">
      Run: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`
      Run: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`
      Goal: 0 errors, 0 NEW warnings, all tests pass.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify grep state">
      Run: Grep pattern="ExecuteAnalysisAsync" glob="**/*.cs"
      Expected post-task: only the declaration in AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs (and possibly remaining test references flagged for task 042 cleanup). Document the count.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `/code-review` on the modified call sites + tests. Run `/adr-check` against ADR-013 + ADR-029 + ADR-038 + bff-extensions.md.
      Fix any findings before commit.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Publish + size check (NFR-01 partial — running tally toward task 047 wave check)">
      Run: dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish-task041/
      Measure compressed size; document delta vs prior baseline. Expected: NEGATIVE (small shrink from removed call sites).
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 041 status complete; advance current-task.md to task 042.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Commit">
      Commit migrated call sites + test updates with conventional message.
      Example: refactor(bff/r7): migrate non-chat ExecuteAnalysisAsync callers to IInvokePlaybookAi (Wave 4 task 041, FR-11)
      If verification-only (no callers found beyond chat-summarize): document explicitly and commit a notes update only.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read (caller-audit doc + each caller source + reference SessionSummarizeOrchestrator)</tool>
